The paper deals with caching, which is a problem in information theory and networking. The paper also mentions content-delivery networks, which falls under the category of networked systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the optimization of caching schemes, which involves algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with communication networks and their performance, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) possible sub-categories.
